        <headline>Heat Advisory issued July 27 at 8:49PM EDT until July 28 at 2:00AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Heat index values up to 105.

* WHERE...Eastern McDowell, Greater Burke, and Greater Caldwell
Counties.

* WHEN...Until 2 AM EDT Monday.

* IMPACTS...Hot temperatures and high humidity may cause heat
illnesses.
</description>
        <instruction>Do not leave young children and pets in unattended vehicles. Car
interiors will reach lethal temperatures in a matter of minutes.

Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.</instruction>
